#!/usr/bin/env Python3

# Systemd Unit file has three sections in [brackets] - Unit - Service - Install
# The unit pertains to a webserver (apache)
# Wants = http-init.service ...wants outlines that something else is required before this unit file can start up
# there is also BEFORE and AFTER ..After=network.target remote-fs.target nss-lookup.target http-init.service
# Documentation=man:http.service(8)

# [Service] - has config unit, these decide what should happen when the system start up
# Type=notify - notify waits for systemd to tell it is ready
# Environment=LAND=C
# ExecStart=/usr/sbin/http $OPTIONS

# [Install]
# WantedBy=multi-user.target - multi user target means the system may have reached a stage where multi users may use the system, if not , they cannot use it.
